Package: gspy
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Forensic goroutine-to-syscall inspector for Go processes
 gspy attaches to a running Go process by PID using eBPF uprobes and 
 kernel tracepoints. It maps goroutine IDs to active syscalls and 
 user-space stack frames in real-time, without ptrace or instrumentation.
 .
 Key features:
  * Zero-footprint forensic inspection.
  * Real-time GID -> Syscall mapping.
  * User-space stack frame resolution via ELF symbol table.
  * Forensic readonly mode with SHA-256 binary verification.
  * Low overhead eBPF-based polling.
